Package org.block.project.block

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Block
    A Block is a shape that can have specific functions with code attached to it.
    Block.AttachableBlock
    If the Block requires additional information to function properly that is in code form, then it should implement Attachable.
    Block.AttachableBlock.StatementBlock  
    Block.CalledBlock
    If your code requires calls to be added into the output code project, then this should be implemented.
    Block.CalledBlock.CodeStartBlock
    If the code provided is a method, constructor
    Block.LinkedBlock
    If a block is directly affected by another block then the former should implement this.
    Block.SpecificSectionBlock
    If the block has specific sections to add to the chooser, then it requires to implement this.
    Block.TextBlock
    If the Block has some text to be shown then this should be implemented Most blocks will implement this
    Block.ValueBlock<V>
    If the block has a output value, then this should be implemented which will allow the Block to be added as a parameter.
    Block.ValueBlock.ConnectedValueBlock<V>  
    Block.ValueBlock.ConnectedValueBlock.MutableConnectedValueBlock<V>  
    BlockType<B extends Block>
    The BlockType provides global data between all Blocks it produces.
    Shapes
    Assists with building common shapes.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractBlock
    The most common implementation for a Block, while this does not provided all functions, it does provided majority of the default functions.
    ShapeTest  
    ShapeTest.PolyTest
